@denimtears is back with another easy summer lineup, this time modeled by @sideshow127, @sexafterchurch, and @anysiakym. ⁠
⁠
The collection keeps things simple with graphic tees, Cotton Wreath shorts, mesh shorts, bags, caps, and other warm-weather essentials that fit right into the season. The collection drops today online and in-store via Denim Tears.

What did fashion look like before the algorithm took over? @derekblasberg’s new book, Fast + Louche, collects photographs he shot for his Interview magazine column of the same name between 2009 and 2012. Now a contributing editor at Harper’s Bazaar, Blasberg captured the social scene that defined fashion, art, and downtown New York during the late aughts and early 2010s—a fleeting moment just before social media transformed the industry.
At the link in bio, Blasberg talks to Harper’s Bazaar editor at large @smooallem, who served as Interview’s editor in chief during that era, to reflect on some of the people, parties, and cultural moments that shaped that period in fashion.
@derekblasberg, with @ParisHilton, @NickyHilton, and Carlos Lopez at a party at Paris Hilton’s house, November 8, 2009.
@thelsd and André Leon Talley at Caviar Kaspia in Paris, July 1, 2009.
@derekblasberg, right with @christbollen and @chloessevigny in front of the Gateway Arch in St. Louise, April 17, 2010.
@katemossagency at The Ritz Paris, May 17, 2011.
@AlexaChung in the East Village in New York, November 6, 2011.
Karl Lagerfeld with Daphne Guinness in Lagerfeld’s studio in Paris, May 17, 2011.
Valentino and @nataliavodianova at a summer party at Valentino’s home, Château de Wideville, July 7, 2010.
Miuccia Prada and Francesco Vezzoli at the Carlyle in New York, March 15, 2010.
@KarlieKloss at a Fashion Week party in Paris, September 30, 2011.
